        <caption>
          <p><bold>Validation of the circRNA isoforms in different gene loci predicted by CIRCexplorer2 but missed by CircAST</bold> The schematic models of circRNA isoforms of Drc7 (Chr8:95,061,713–95,062,395) <bold>(A)</bold>, <italic>Uggt2</italic> (Chr14:118,994,946–119,002,986) <bold>(B)</bold>, <italic>Agtpbp1</italic> (Chr13:59,473,688–59,482,604) <bold>(C)</bold>, Adam3 (Chr8:24,719,415–24,725,361) <bold>(D)</bold>, <italic>Lin54</italic> (Chr5:100,475,689–100,485,855) <bold>(E)</bold>, Usp32 (Chr11:85,017,630–85,022,905) <bold>(F)</bold>, <italic>Mllt10</italic> (Chr2:18,101,458–18,126,229) <bold>(G)</bold>, and <italic>Scaper</italic> (Chr9:55,912,040–55,921,338) <bold>(H)</bold> are provided separately (on the left). The RT-PCR results for each circRNA isoform showing incorrect product size are provided separately (on the right). These eight circRNA isoforms failed validation.</p>
